text: Scirpophaga phaedima is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Ian Francis Bell Common in 1960. It is found in northern Australia. The wingspan is 22–40 mm. Both the forewings and hindwings are white. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1960 Category:Schoenobiinae Category:Moths of Australia
title: Scirpophaga phaedima
